1
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:12,333
<i> We need to catch that guy</i>

2
00:00:12,467 --> 00:00:16,267
<i>so we can find out who let
Monty and Mando escape.</i>

3
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:19,133
<i>Well, Mira, that's good
journalism, but I'm sorry.</i>

4
00:00:19,267 --> 00:00:20,333
<i> I only approve of it,</i>

5
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:21,400
<i>but when it comes to the
construction,</i>

6
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:22,833
<i>I'm no longer part of it.
But don't worry,</i>

7
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:24,033
<i> I'll get to the bottom of it.</i>

8
00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:25,800
<i>The road project
I'm investigating,</i>

9
00:00:25,933 --> 00:00:27,500
<i> Jake, it's a ghost project.</i>

10
00:00:27,633 --> 00:00:29,367
<i> Noble, that's not our job.</i>

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:30,467
<i> That's under the Ombudsman.</i>

12
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,100
<i>Don't we have a lot
of gay friends?</i>

13
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:33,967
<i>- Yes.
- I just want to warn them</i>

14
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:35,633
<i> about this serial killer.</i>

15
00:00:35,767 --> 00:00:37,600
<i>It's the same,
it's the same as your brother.</i>

16
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:38,833
<i>He was stabbed
with an icepick, too.</i>

17
00:00:38,967 --> 00:00:41,300
<i>When I told the police
who the suspect was,</i>

18
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:42,867
<i> they didn't believe me.</i>

19
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,100
<i> Do you have a suspect?</i>

20
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:46,433
<i>It's Matmat! Maybe his mother
is hiding him.</i>

21
00:00:46,567 --> 00:00:47,867
<i> You can go to his house.</i>

22
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,633
<i> Where can we find that street?</i>

23
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:50,967
<i> It's impossible in San Rafael.</i>

24
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:53,733
<i>There's Casa Rafael Avenue
south of Calabari.</i>

25
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:55,667
<i>Are you sure
we're on the right street?</i>

26
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,433
<i> He moved years ago.</i>

27
00:00:57,567 --> 00:01:00,733
<i>And I think
that is the correct street.</i>

28
00:01:00,867 --> 00:01:02,200
<i> Send me your account now.</i>

29
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:03,867
<i> I'll pay you after this call.</i>

30
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,233
<i> Pay your face.</i>

31
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:07,767
<i> Goodbye 100k.</i>

32
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:13,633
Oh my, it's so dead.

33
00:01:13,767 --> 00:01:14,900
Condolences, Madam.

34
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:17,100
We sympathize.
Is there soup?

35
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:18,400
Are you sure, huh?

36
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:20,433
This needs treatment.
Change color.

37
00:01:22,967 --> 00:01:24,067
Freddie!

38
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:29,467
Abdul, Marcy, it's been a while

39
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,767
It's been a long time.

40
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:31,900
Sorry!

41
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:35,033
You know, we're busy
in the village.

42
00:01:35,167 --> 00:01:36,667
What, are you getting a haircut?

43
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,300
I have the best haircutter.

44
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:41,100
Here's my assistant hairstylist,
and her name is...

45
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:42,467
Badong.

46
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:44,933
<i> Is that funny?</i>

47
00:01:45,067 --> 00:01:47,100
Hey, those are my friends.

48
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:48,600
What, are you getting a haircut?

49
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:51,000
You didn't tell me Aquaman
was your barber.

50
00:01:51,133 --> 00:01:53,233
- Aquaman...
- I'm sorry.

51
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:55,367
That's my friend!

52
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:56,967
- I'm your boss.
- So Aquaman.

53
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,433
Come on, let's go to the beach.

54
00:01:58,567 --> 00:02:03,600
That's why we came here,
because we're going to gossip.

55
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:07,567
We know that all the gossip
goes through you.

56
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:09,867
When it comes to gossip,
I'm the first one?

57
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,233
But that's right.

58
00:02:11,367 --> 00:02:13,300
When it comes to gossip,
I'm number one there!

59
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:16,033
Yes!

60
00:02:16,167 --> 00:02:18,733
Speaking of gossip, that serial
killer who stabbed the gay.

61
00:02:18,867 --> 00:02:20,633
Oh my, if he did it to me,
I would really stab him!

62
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:22,000
Calm down!

63
00:02:22,133 --> 00:02:24,967
- I'll shoot him again.
- Badong, we have a customer!

64
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:26,233
Stop!

65
00:02:26,367 --> 00:02:28,100
Sorry, Madam!
Sorry!

66
00:02:28,233 --> 00:02:31,033
Calm down. Maybe the serial
killer is just around the area.

67
00:02:31,167 --> 00:02:32,500
Oh my god.

68
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:07,567
<i> This is nothing, Bess.</i>

69
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:15,800
What's your problem?

70
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,033
Why?

71
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,900
I'm just doing our job.

72
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,067
But you shouldn't do that.

73
00:03:21,233 --> 00:03:23,100
The manager almost felt so small
from where she was standing.

74
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:24,300
Can you imagine?

75
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:25,833
They erased evidence

76
00:03:25,967 --> 00:03:27,833
just because they got paid
by insurance.

77
00:03:29,433 --> 00:03:31,033
Can't you hear yourself?

78
00:03:32,067 --> 00:03:34,800
We've barely started here,
and you're already hyper.

79
00:03:35,267 --> 00:03:38,133
Our investigation into
this fugitive has just begun.

80
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,800
You know,
you won't understand me

81
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:42,867
because you have no competition
in your body.

82
00:03:43,133 --> 00:03:44,433
So this is about Bobby again?

83
00:03:44,567 --> 00:03:45,800
Yes.

84
00:03:45,933 --> 00:03:47,967
That's why I need
to close this case.

85
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,567
Charlie, the guy, is still
on a desk job.

86
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:51,933
Exactly.

87
00:03:52,067 --> 00:03:55,400
Maybe Bobby will outsmart me,
ruin my reputation,

88
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:56,867
even though she's just
on a desk job.

89
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:11,733
- Dude.
- Hey, Dude.

90
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:13,433
Here's your suit.

91
00:04:13,567 --> 00:04:15,033
I had it washed it too.

92
00:04:15,167 --> 00:04:16,900
Are you sure you washed it?

93
00:04:18,933 --> 00:04:20,400
Wait, Dude. It looks like
you didn't wash it.

94
00:04:20,533 --> 00:04:21,533
It smells like sweat!

95
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:23,200
It's so expensive to have it
dry-cleaned!

96
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:24,867
Maybe it's just you
who washed it.

97
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,367
I think I got scammed, Dude.

98
00:04:28,533 --> 00:04:29,933
But I've already had it
dry-cleaned!

99
00:04:31,267 --> 00:04:32,333
It's annoying.

100
00:04:32,467 --> 00:04:33,800
Wait.

101
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:35,133
What happened last night?

102
00:04:35,267 --> 00:04:36,167
Is it okay?

103
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,767
That's the thing, Dude.

104
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:40,933
It seems like his brother
doesn't like me.

105
00:04:41,067 --> 00:04:43,033
Why? How did Faye
introduce you?

106
00:04:43,167 --> 00:04:45,167
"Brother, this is my plus one."

107
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:46,200
Plus one?

108
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:47,900
What's that, Dude?
Plus one?

109
00:04:49,033 --> 00:04:49,900
You know, that's nothing.

110
00:04:50,033 --> 00:04:51,567
At least, she introduced you.

111
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:54,433
I don't know,
maybe I'm just being paranoid.

112
00:04:56,933 --> 00:05:00,100
Hey, does Boss Tonyo
have an assignment for us?

113
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:02,700
Sir Tonyo said
there's nothing yet.

114
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:04,533
He said we're just on standby
if needed.

115
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:06,867
Okay.

116
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:09,800
Do you want some coffee?
My treat.

117
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:13,133
Coffee, P120!

118
00:05:13,267 --> 00:05:14,533
Dude, that's only five pesos
in our area.

119
00:05:14,667 --> 00:05:16,567
Just put in a coin,
you've got coffee.

120
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:17,967
You know, you're really jologs.

121
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:19,133
Just have coffee in your area.

122
00:05:19,267 --> 00:05:20,500
Okay, Dude, I'll have...

123
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,133
Café Latek.

124
00:05:23,267 --> 00:05:24,267
Café latte.

125
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:27,267
- Okay, that's it. Is that it.
- That's it? Sure?

126
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,100
All right.

127
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:36,767
We need to ask you
something first.

128
00:05:36,933 --> 00:05:38,733
What?

129
00:05:38,867 --> 00:05:40,633
What's that?
So you're grilling me?

130
00:05:40,967 --> 00:05:42,533
Oh my, I know you're style.

131
00:05:42,667 --> 00:05:43,567
Okay, go ahead.

132
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:44,900
I have nothing to hide.

133
00:05:45,033 --> 00:05:46,800
Okay.

134
00:05:46,933 --> 00:05:50,167
Have you ever cheated on
your partner, like ever?

135
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:51,300
Wait a minute, Marcy.

136
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:53,567
Your questions are making me
feel like Inday Badiday.

137
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,500
Inday Badiday? It's so old!

138
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:56,833
Tito Boy is the in thing now.

139
00:05:56,967 --> 00:05:57,833
Inday Badiday?

140
00:05:57,967 --> 00:05:59,700
Hey, Friend, focus on that.

141
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:00,900
Cut her hair.

142
00:06:01,033 --> 00:06:03,000
Hey friend, you have a lot
of angst!

143
00:06:03,133 --> 00:06:04,400
Answer me first!

144
00:06:04,533 --> 00:06:06,067
No. You know, I just don't want
to answer

145
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,733
because I know what will happen
here.

146
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:08,967
You're going to quote me,

147
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:10,500
and you're going to use it
against me.

148
00:06:10,633 --> 00:06:11,833
I don't want,
I'm used to that.

149
00:06:11,967 --> 00:06:13,867
You're a fool
because you don't understand.

150
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,633
Friend, believe us.

151
00:06:15,767 --> 00:06:18,267
Well, based on our police
friend,

152
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,567
she said this isn't just
a hate crime.

153
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:22,900
There's a pattern.

154
00:06:23,033 --> 00:06:24,000
- Pattern?
- Yes.

155
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:25,500
What's the pattern?
What's this? Bingo?

156
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:26,667
What's the pattern?
You're saying there's a pattern?

157
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:30,933
Well, the killer is targeting
either a cheater,

158
00:06:31,067 --> 00:06:33,967
an abusive parent,
or a scammer.

159
00:06:42,367 --> 00:06:44,000
Mira,

160
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:45,267
Chief's right.

161
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,300
This is outside our jurisdiction

162
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:50,067
unless there's a connected
criminal case.

163
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,700
That's what I'm saying.

164
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:52,967
I'm expecting that.

165
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:54,067
What's your plan?

166
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:58,133
I need to talk
to the contractors.

167
00:06:58,567 --> 00:07:01,300
I need to know if Mayor Glen
is really involved

168
00:07:01,433 --> 00:07:02,800
in this ghost project.

169
00:07:02,933 --> 00:07:04,667
Do you want me
to come with you?

170
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:06,567
No, you might get scolded.

171
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:07,433
No.

172
00:07:07,567 --> 00:07:09,733
I also want to make sure
you're safe.

173
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:10,800
Are you sure?

174
00:07:11,867 --> 00:07:13,400
What? Let's go?

175
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:14,500
Oh, okay.

176
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:16,367
Ma'am Bobby...

177
00:07:17,967 --> 00:07:20,267
The Chief wants to see you
when you arrive.

178
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:21,667
He said to go to his office.

179
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:25,667
Okay, thank you.

180
00:07:27,633 --> 00:07:29,433
Let's go?

181
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:30,633
Let's go.

182
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:47,900
Enriquez, come in.

183
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,133
Why are you late?

184
00:07:57,167 --> 00:07:58,733
You might be forgetting,
Enriquez,

185
00:07:58,867 --> 00:07:59,967
you have a desk job.

186
00:08:02,433 --> 00:08:03,867
I'm sorry, Sir.

187
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:12,433
There's a lead
I'm following.

188
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:16,767
Lead?

189
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:20,200
Did I hear you right?

190
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,300
Maybe you want me to file

191
00:08:23,433 --> 00:08:24,900
an insubordination case
against you.

192
00:08:25,033 --> 00:08:26,433
Chief, just a moment.

193
00:08:26,567 --> 00:08:28,100
Listen to me first.

194
00:08:29,267 --> 00:08:32,800
Noble and I saw a pattern
with the icepick killer.

195
00:08:32,933 --> 00:08:35,500
This is not just a hate crime.

196
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:40,167
He has specific targets,
not just gay people.

197
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:43,600
Chief, this is a serial killer
we're looking for.

198
00:08:47,867 --> 00:08:49,333
Enriquez,

199
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:54,400
make a consolidated report
of everything you've dug up.

200
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:56,067
Yes, Sir.

201
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,700
And give it to Conde.

202
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:03,067
And let me remind you,

203
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:06,200
you're assigned to a desk job,

204
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:08,700
and give everything to Conde

205
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:11,033
because he's in charge
of this case.

206
00:09:11,167 --> 00:09:12,067
But, Sir...

207
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:14,333
Give everything to Conde.

208
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,733
Okay, Sir.

209
00:09:37,433 --> 00:09:38,833
Thanks for coming with me.

210
00:09:39,867 --> 00:09:41,667
But this is the last one.

211
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,067
Why?

212
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:46,000
Of course, I don't want Chief
to get mad at you.

213
00:09:46,133 --> 00:09:48,467
It seems like I'm a bad
influence on you.

214
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,633
Oh my.

215
00:09:49,767 --> 00:09:53,367
If they think that way,
they're so wrong.

216
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:56,067
I work even harder
because of you.

217
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,233
Look.

218
00:09:57,367 --> 00:09:59,900
Even though it's not my job,
I do it.

219
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,967
I'm serious, Jake.

220
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:05,300
Sorry.

221
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:08,733
I'm serious, too.

222
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,000
Actually,

223
00:10:13,133 --> 00:10:15,600
I want to introduce you
to my parents.

224
00:10:18,033 --> 00:10:19,800
I'm that serious, Mira.

225
00:10:26,233 --> 00:10:27,600
What do you think?

226
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:29,533
Are you thinking about it?

227
00:10:29,667 --> 00:10:31,333
You're thinking about
your backstory, aren't you?

228
00:10:31,467 --> 00:10:32,367
Crazy.

229
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:34,733
I'm a good girl.

230
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,500
What I'm worried about,

231
00:10:36,633 --> 00:10:39,800
I have a lot of friends
who are cheaters.

232
00:10:39,933 --> 00:10:44,233
Although they're not scammers
or abusive parents.

233
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:46,733
This Mar, he's a scammer.

234
00:10:46,867 --> 00:10:48,533
He never paid his debts before.

235
00:10:48,667 --> 00:10:49,933
- Oh my god!
- You're so thick-faced, Abdul.

236
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:51,567
- It's true!
- You?

237
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:54,967
No, I'll pay my debts.

238
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:58,233
But it went with the Afam.

239
00:10:58,533 --> 00:10:59,967
So you're going to run away
from it?

240
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:01,567
You didn't pay?

241
00:11:01,833 --> 00:11:03,800
Well, you can't run.
Your legs are short.

242
00:11:03,933 --> 00:11:05,233
<i>True.
It's hard.</i>

243
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:07,100
Stop it.

244
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:08,833
You know, I have to call
my friends.

245
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,967
I need to warn them.

246
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:12,500
They need that.

247
00:11:12,633 --> 00:11:14,133
Yes, do that, please.

248
00:11:19,433 --> 00:11:20,900
You'll also warn them

249
00:11:21,033 --> 00:11:23,333
that there might be strangers
around, okay?

250
00:11:23,467 --> 00:11:25,000
Okay, okay,
I'll just call them.

251
00:11:25,133 --> 00:11:27,567
If I get any info,
I'll tell you.

252
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:29,033
Thank you.

253
00:11:29,167 --> 00:11:30,067
Just wait.

254
00:11:32,433 --> 00:11:33,267
Beshie...

255
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:24,967
Hey...

256
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,533
It's like you saw a ghost.

257
00:12:26,767 --> 00:12:27,767
What happened to you?

258
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:30,167
Nothing, nothing.

259
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,600
I just thought...

260
00:12:31,733 --> 00:12:33,433
But...

261
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:34,867
It's nothing, nothing.

262
00:12:46,033 --> 00:12:48,300
What's your plan, Mayor?

263
00:12:48,467 --> 00:12:51,667
Boss, you want me to take down
that reporter!

264
00:12:53,467 --> 00:12:55,467
You know, Dante...

265
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,733
Boss...

266
00:12:56,867 --> 00:12:57,900
I'll do it.

267
00:13:00,067 --> 00:13:01,100
Dante, it's like this.

268
00:13:01,233 --> 00:13:02,833
I'll repeat it for you, okay?

269
00:13:03,067 --> 00:13:05,367
If something happens
to that reporter,

270
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:06,967
the problem will go back to...

271
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:09,667
Mayor.

272
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,933
Do you understand?

273
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:14,467
Okay, Boss.

274
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:15,900
Okay?

275
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:18,700
Put that in your brain.

276
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,133
But this is my fault.

277
00:13:23,300 --> 00:13:26,867
I didn't even think he could ask
the police for help.

278
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:30,067
Regan caught it,
your guy inside.

279
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,833
Well, he's useful too.

280
00:13:33,833 --> 00:13:34,933
Never mind.

281
00:13:36,467 --> 00:13:38,533
I've prepared
for this situation.

282
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,367
Where is the engineer
I asked you to find?

283
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:46,133
Boss, I know where he's hiding.

284
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:49,033
You said something right.

285
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,733
Go get him.

286
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,067
Thank you.

287
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:06,933
Excuse me.

288
00:14:07,067 --> 00:14:09,167
Can we talk to the owner?

289
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:13,100
Boss isn't here.

290
00:14:13,233 --> 00:14:15,533
Do you know
where we can see him?

291
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,633
We just have some questions
for him.

292
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:18,900
Oh my, Ma'am, I'm sorry.

293
00:14:19,033 --> 00:14:20,333
I don't know where Boss is.

294
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:21,800
What is this about?

295
00:14:26,633 --> 00:14:29,000
Okay, we'll go back next time.

296
00:14:29,167 --> 00:14:30,333
Thank you.

297
00:14:30,467 --> 00:14:31,433
Thank you.

298
00:14:37,867 --> 00:14:38,933
What do you think?

299
00:14:40,633 --> 00:14:44,133
That's how they really move,
delaying tactic.

300
00:14:44,433 --> 00:14:45,900
I have a feeling
they've been warned.

301
00:14:48,433 --> 00:14:49,400
What, let's go?

302
00:14:50,767 --> 00:14:51,733
Let's go.

303
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,033
Sister, here's the payment.

304
00:14:55,533 --> 00:14:56,400
Here's your hange.

305
00:14:56,533 --> 00:14:57,933
Thank you.

306
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,700
The umbrella is nice.

307
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:13,733
Yeah, I didn't know our gossip
would be relevant.

308
00:15:13,867 --> 00:15:14,967
- Yes.
- Our friend

309
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:15,900
is still talking to someone.

310
00:15:16,033 --> 00:15:17,400
This could save your life.

311
00:15:17,533 --> 00:15:19,767
Okay, update me anytime.

312
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:20,833
Okay.

313
00:15:20,967 --> 00:15:23,100
- Hey, girl!
- Oh, what now?

314
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:24,267
We have to go.

315
00:15:24,533 --> 00:15:26,800
We still need to visit Abdul's
friend in the other village.

316
00:15:26,933 --> 00:15:28,633
Okay, as long as you know
what to do.

317
00:15:28,767 --> 00:15:29,933
Spread the word.

318
00:15:30,067 --> 00:15:33,033
The whole sisterhood needs
to hear about it, okay?

319
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:34,933
That's our mission, friend.

320
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:36,467
Badong, they're leaving.

321
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:37,500
- Sis...
- What's with you?

322
00:15:37,633 --> 00:15:38,800
Don't touch each other..

323
00:15:38,933 --> 00:15:39,833
It's you.

324
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:41,967
- What is it?
- Go ahead.

325
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:44,067
- Be careful, be careful.
- Girl, we'll go ahead.

326
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,033
Call me, okay?

327
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:46,400
Be careful.

328
00:15:46,533 --> 00:15:47,767
Where's my umbrella?

329
00:15:48,867 --> 00:15:50,067
Friend, someone stole it.

330
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,800
That was too beautiful.

331
00:15:51,933 --> 00:15:53,567
My god. It's only P150,
it got stolen.

332
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:54,633
Let's go!

333
00:15:54,767 --> 00:15:57,900
Friend, just buy a new one.
You're so stingy.

334
00:15:58,033 --> 00:15:59,133
You took it, didn't you?

335
00:15:59,267 --> 00:16:02,000
No. I'm done with that
already.

336
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:26,900
What's your plan, Bok?

337
00:16:27,033 --> 00:16:28,900
Let's search the entire street.

338
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:32,900
We need to know what rainbow
Alma is talking about.

339
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,267
But how?

340
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,400
There are so many
rainbow colors here.

341
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,700
Who among them
will be the next victim?

342
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:05,833
Madam Alma...

343
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:09,033
Are you still not okay?

344
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:10,833
You've been like that
since the other day.

345
00:17:10,967 --> 00:17:14,367
Please, I'm concentrating here!

346
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,367
I need to remember something!

347
00:17:17,467 --> 00:17:19,000
Just go downstairs for now!

348
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:20,833
Sorry, sorry.

349
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:46,267
It's Alma.

350
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,367
Hello, Alma?

351
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:51,733
Hello, Sir Tonyo?

352
00:17:51,867 --> 00:17:53,467
Yes, we've figured out
the street.

353
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,600
We're here at Casa Rafael
Avenue now,

354
00:17:55,733 --> 00:17:59,167
but maybe you can help us.

355
00:17:59,567 --> 00:18:01,533
There are a lot of rainbow
designs scattered around here.

356
00:18:01,767 --> 00:18:03,733
We don't really know
what to look for.

357
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:06,200
Sir, that's what
I'm calling you about.

358
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:07,700
My vision is clear.

359
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:09,767
What I'm talking about
with the rainbow design,

360
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:11,000
it's an umbrella!

361
00:18:11,133 --> 00:18:12,033
What?

362
00:18:12,167 --> 00:18:13,933
Umbrella?

363
00:18:14,067 --> 00:18:15,333
Are you sure, Alma?

364
00:18:15,467 --> 00:18:17,367
Yes, Sir, I'm sure!

365
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:20,033
Okay, okay,
thank you very much.

366
00:18:20,167 --> 00:18:21,667
That's a big help, Alma.

367
00:18:23,967 --> 00:18:24,967
What is it?

368
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:26,100
Umbrella.

369
00:18:28,133 --> 00:18:29,833
Umbrella with a rainbow design.

370
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,633
That's what we're looking for.

371
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:43,467
This, this, this, this, this.

372
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,467
This is for Mister.

373
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:46,067
Sister, where's my change?

374
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,467
Oh, yeah, wait, wait.

375
00:18:53,433 --> 00:18:55,467
Who ordered the orange?
Yours, right?

376
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:57,167
- Wait.
- Miss,

377
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:58,200
your change is not enough.

378
00:18:58,333 --> 00:18:59,167
Not enough?

379
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:00,767
I gave you three fifty-peso
bills.

380
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:02,767
What three?
Well, these are just two.

381
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:06,633
Let me see.

382
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:08,667
Only three? That's three.

383
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,833
Miss, you're so kind.

384
00:19:13,967 --> 00:19:16,000
Bless your heart.

385
00:19:36,933 --> 00:19:37,933
There!

386
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:53,933
The target is already there.

387
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:59,400
I'm sure the killer
is also around the area.

388
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:01,567
Let's just follow the target.

389
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:02,367
Who are you?

390
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:09,833
Help!

391
00:21:10,267 --> 00:21:12,033
Stop that!
Raise your hand!

392
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:30,567
I dug up the financial report
of the construction company

393
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:33,100
that owns that ghost project
you're talking about.

394
00:21:33,233 --> 00:21:35,467
How did you know we were
investigating something?

395
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,500
The Mayor is really good!

396
00:21:37,633 --> 00:21:38,667
That's right!

397
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:42,767
Reward for those who want
to find that gay killer.

398
00:21:42,933 --> 00:21:44,733
But I still don't want
that Glen!

399
00:21:44,867 --> 00:21:46,300
I know I owe you a lot,

400
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:49,333
but maybe you can give me one
more chance, Boss!

401
00:21:49,467 --> 00:21:51,200
Goodbye, Engineer Marasigan.

402
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:52,500
- No, Boss!
- See you in hell.

403
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:55,267
Do you have a photo
of Matmat there?

404
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:57,800
I do, but it's an old picture.

405
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:59,267
This is Mateo Ramos.

406
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,167
Yes.

407
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:03,700
Matmat's real name
is Mateo Ramos.

408
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:04,933
Hello, Sir Tonyo?

409
00:22:05,067 --> 00:22:07,200
I know what the killer
looks like.

410
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:08,367
Can we talk?

411
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:09,800
Let's go have a snack first.

412
00:22:09,933 --> 00:22:11,033
Conde!

413
00:22:11,167 --> 00:22:12,433
It's good that you're here.

414
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:14,000
Do you want us to have dinner?
